WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:03.086
<i>The Trivantians have no queen or king.</i>

2
00:00:03.170 --> 00:00:04.922
<i>I cannot negotiate
with common politicians.</i>

3
00:00:05.005 --> 00:00:06.340
Of course not.

4
00:00:06.423 --> 00:00:08.175
<i>But I can go as your emissary.</i>

5
00:00:08.258 --> 00:00:10.594
I need to be able to defend my family.

6
00:00:10.677 --> 00:00:13.180
I'm sure the princess can appoint you
a proper trainer.

7
00:00:13.263 --> 00:00:14.431
I'll ask her to appoint you.

8
00:00:14.515 --> 00:00:16.265
<i>I'm Harlan. Lord of Pennsa.</i>

9
00:00:16.350 --> 00:00:19.520
and this is awkward.
but I'm married to your wife.

10
00:00:20.854 --> 00:00:23.315
<i>The Triangle offer the Payans
an overture for peace.</i>

11
00:00:23.398 --> 00:00:26.443
<i>The peace talks will fail.
and we will make sure they do.</i>

12
00:00:26.527 --> 00:00:29.112
If something goes wrong.
they will lay the blame at your feet.

13
00:00:29.196 --> 00:00:31.240
Which is why you will go in my place.

14
00:00:31.323 --> 00:00:33.283
<i>Maybe having God on your side means</i>

15
00:00:33.367 --> 00:00:36.411
you win the war
without having to fight the battle.

16
00:00:36.495 --> 00:00:39.915
As long as your sister is on the throne.
there will be no peace.

17
00:00:39.998 --> 00:00:42.334
<i>She's protecting her people.
Isn't that what queens do?</i>

18
00:00:42.417 --> 00:00:44.962
Why are you defending someone
who hunted us our whole lives?

19
00:00:45.045 --> 00:00:47.047
<i>It's a secret. Kofun.</i>

20
00:00:47.130 --> 00:00:48.131
It must stay between us.

21
00:00:48.215 --> 00:00:51.343
This satchel hung on the saddle
with a message for you.

22
00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:59.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

23
00:01:10.293 --> 00:01:12.295
- Paris.
<i>- Help! We've been betrayed!</i>

24
00:01:12.379 --> 00:01:14.256
- Paris.
<i>- Intruders! Wake up!</i>

25
00:01:14.339 --> 00:01:15.757
Paris!

26
00:01:15.841 --> 00:01:19.219
Haniwa. Haniwa.

27
00:01:19.302 --> 00:01:22.139
Your mother. Baba. They must not leave.

28
00:01:22.222 --> 00:01:24.099
They've already left. What's wrong?

29
00:01:25.100 --> 00:01:26.601
I dreamt betrayal.

30
00:01:29.020 --> 00:01:32.899
Blood. Blood and betrayal. Haniwa.

31
00:01:36.653 --> 00:01:39.072
Okay. You stay.

32
00:01:43.994 --> 00:01:45.495
Can't you just send someone else?

33
00:01:45.579 --> 00:01:48.540
Who should I send?
Do you want me to trust a Witchfinder?

34
00:01:48.623 --> 00:01:50.167
Can you even ride a horse?

35
00:01:50.250 --> 00:01:51.835
Kofun does it. How hard can it be?

36
00:01:51.918 --> 00:01:54.588
-That's it. I'm coming with you.
-You'll just slow me down.

37
00:01:54.671 --> 00:01:56.590
-Just grab me a horse!
-Charlotte!

38
00:01:57.549 --> 00:01:58.842
There's no time.

39
00:02:02.345 --> 00:02:05.432
- Swear to me you'll be safe.
- I'll do my best.

40
00:02:07.267 --> 00:02:08.268
I promise.

41
00:03:52.164 --> 00:03:53.540
Keep to yourself.

42
00:03:54.458 --> 00:03:56.293
Pay attention to all that is said.

43
00:03:58.211 --> 00:04:00.589
I don't see how an agreement
will be reached. but…

44
00:04:01.631 --> 00:04:05.469
if you feel our delegates weakening.
you will make them see reason.

45
00:04:06.845 --> 00:04:07.846
Yes. sir.

46
00:04:12.100 --> 00:04:13.101
You're troubled.

47
00:04:15.937 --> 00:04:18.190
I understand the queen wants war.

48
00:04:19.024 --> 00:04:21.902
but an attempt at peace costs us nothing.

49
00:04:21.985 --> 00:04:25.489
Every day we wait to strike
is another day she grows her forces.

50
00:04:26.364 --> 00:04:28.617
I've buried enough soldiers this year.

51
00:04:28.700 --> 00:04:30.994
You represent me
at the conference.

52
00:04:32.245 --> 00:04:35.707
The other delegates will be wary of you.
but they will also listen to you.

53
00:04:36.208 --> 00:04:37.876
No one will listen to a lieutenant.

54
00:04:41.797 --> 00:04:45.258
That is why I am making you a captain.

55
00:04:54.309 --> 00:04:56.478
The Payans have killed our people.

56
00:04:56.561 --> 00:04:58.438
And instead of avenging their deaths.

57
00:04:58.522 --> 00:05:01.525
the Triangle would prefer
that we appease the enemy.

58
00:05:03.193 --> 00:05:04.194
Wren.

59
00:05:04.945 --> 00:05:08.782
Sometimes in order to best serve
the republic.

60
00:05:08.865 --> 00:05:10.534
you must work around its government.

61
00:05:11.576 --> 00:05:14.538
The talks must fail. Do you understand?

62
00:05:15.288 --> 00:05:16.289
Yes. sir.

63
00:05:18.834 --> 00:05:21.002
The delegation is leaving. Here.

64
00:05:22.295 --> 00:05:23.547
In case you get hungry.

65
00:06:25.567 --> 00:06:26.693
Are you okay?

66
00:06:27.694 --> 00:06:30.906
Kerrigan was always gonna
get himself killed one way or another.

67
00:06:33.575 --> 00:06:38.163
I'm pleased he did it
in the service of the princess. my wife…

68
00:06:39.915 --> 00:06:43.460
not crossing the border with a bag
of thornflowers stuck up his ass.

69
00:06:48.757 --> 00:06:50.092
I need another drink.

70
00:06:51.176 --> 00:06:54.429
We can drink later
when we toast the Trivantian delegation.

71
00:06:54.513 --> 00:06:57.307
You can toast those bastards.
I'm drinking to my brother.

72
00:06:57.390 --> 00:06:58.975
-Harlan. We--
-Sorry.

73
00:06:59.580 --> 00:07:01.749
You have nothing to be sorry for.

74
00:07:02.646 --> 00:07:05.774
But there's a lot at stake here.
and if you're unable to participate…

75
00:07:05.857 --> 00:07:09.027
-I know what's at stake. It's my city.
-…you have to let me know.

76
00:07:12.656 --> 00:07:13.657
I'm fine.

77
00:07:15.617 --> 00:07:20.288
If we fail. Sibeth will have her war.
and the Trivantians will destroy us.

78
00:07:22.207 --> 00:07:25.460
I just got my family back.
I will not let any harm come to them now.

79
00:07:26.962 --> 00:07:27.963
Nor will I.

80
00:07:34.052 --> 00:07:36.388
Actually.
you're the only family I've got now.

81
00:07:39.015 --> 00:07:40.684
That's pretty sad. huh?

82
00:08:18.722 --> 00:08:20.599
That's 12 heads you've lost today.

83
00:08:20.682 --> 00:08:23.059
-I blocked you twice that time.
-Oh.

84
00:08:23.143 --> 00:08:26.396
We'll tie a knot by your grave
to remember that stunning achievement.

85
00:08:28.106 --> 00:08:31.526
How do you do it?

86
00:08:31.610 --> 00:08:34.196
It's like you know where I'm gonna be
before I do.

87
00:08:34.279 --> 00:08:36.490
Movement is a language. Hmm?

88
00:08:37.240 --> 00:08:39.367
Dance. combat. fucking.

89
00:08:39.868 --> 00:08:42.287
It's all just bodies
talking to each other.

90
00:08:42.954 --> 00:08:45.457
Now. I'm trying to teach you to listen.

91
00:08:45.957 --> 00:08:48.043
but you just keep swatting at my sword.

92
00:08:51.505 --> 00:08:52.506
Cover your eyes.

93
00:08:55.342 --> 00:08:56.760
Don't think I'm ready for this.

94
00:08:56.843 --> 00:08:58.220
Oh. believe me. you're not.

95
00:08:59.096 --> 00:09:00.972
But sight clearly isn't helping you.

96
00:09:01.723 --> 00:09:04.518
So either it's hurting you.
or you're simply hopeless.

97
00:09:05.310 --> 00:09:07.062
I just wanna find out which it is.

98
00:09:07.145 --> 00:09:08.188
Let's go.

99
00:09:20.450 --> 00:09:21.451
Okay.

100
00:09:31.378 --> 00:09:32.379
Dropped my sword--

101
00:09:32.462 --> 00:09:33.505
Stop!

102
00:09:33.587 --> 00:09:34.588
What--

103
00:09:48.019 --> 00:09:49.020
Good news.

104
00:09:49.896 --> 00:09:51.189
You may not be hopeless.

105
00:09:52.357 --> 00:09:54.609
-But we're done training for today.
-No. I wanna go again.

106
00:09:54.693 --> 00:09:56.903
Well. then you better find
someone else to fight.

107
00:10:19.968 --> 00:10:21.470
That is the Payan banner.

108
00:11:25.784 --> 00:11:27.035
Commander Watts

109
00:11:27.119 --> 00:11:29.121
of the Trivantian Empire.

110
00:11:32.457 --> 00:11:34.668
Captain Gosset of the Payan kingdom.

111
00:11:36.002 --> 00:11:38.463
As has been the custom
between our two nations.

112
00:11:38.547 --> 00:11:41.758
soldiers shall maintain their company
outside the camp.

113
00:11:42.384 --> 00:11:45.220
All others who enter will be unarmed.

114
00:11:45.303 --> 00:11:46.304
Agreed.

115
00:11:46.930 --> 00:11:50.100
Our soldiers will check your delegates.
and yours will check ours.

116
00:11:51.143 --> 00:11:52.144
Agreed.

117
00:11:53.270 --> 00:11:54.813
Then let's begin.

118
00:12:03.655 --> 00:12:04.740
Clear.

119
00:12:07.075 --> 00:12:09.369
- Clear.
- Next.

120
00:12:16.460 --> 00:12:17.461
Clear.

121
00:12:22.215 --> 00:12:23.300
Clear.

122
00:12:31.558 --> 00:12:32.559
Clear.

123
00:12:41.067 --> 00:12:42.402
Clear.

124
00:12:55.082 --> 00:12:56.083
Clear.

125
00:12:58.502 --> 00:12:59.503
Clear.

126
00:12:59.586 --> 00:13:00.587
You're fine.

127
00:13:00.670 --> 00:13:03.340
- Arms up. Arms higher. huh?
- Arms up.

128
00:13:06.927 --> 00:13:08.970
- What is this?
- Move on.

129
00:13:13.934 --> 00:13:15.977
Chet-chet.

130
00:13:20.273 --> 00:13:22.943
Haniwa?
What are you doing here?

131
00:13:23.026 --> 00:13:26.905
- I have a message from Paris.
- Shh. Come down here.

132
00:13:26.988 --> 00:13:29.825
- When did you learn to ride?
- I didn't.

133
00:13:29.908 --> 00:13:32.661
- It hurts a lot actually.
- What does Paris say?

134
00:13:32.744 --> 00:13:35.997
She says you will be betrayed.
We should go now.

135
00:13:36.081 --> 00:13:38.583
If we leave the talks.
we are assured of war.

136
00:13:38.667 --> 00:13:39.960
She dreamt it. Mama.

137
00:13:40.043 --> 00:13:41.294
She seemed very sure.

138
00:13:41.378 --> 00:13:43.088
Paris's premonitions might come true.

139
00:13:43.171 --> 00:13:46.007
but if we walk away.
thousands of people will die.

140
00:13:46.091 --> 00:13:47.217
That is a certainty.

141
00:13:49.136 --> 00:13:50.137
Papa.

142
00:13:52.431 --> 00:13:54.391
Your mother will handle our business.

143
00:13:54.474 --> 00:13:57.519
We will stay close
in case this betrayal does come to pass.

144
00:13:59.146 --> 00:14:00.147
Thank you.

145
00:14:04.109 --> 00:14:05.360
She has been wrong before.

146
00:14:05.861 --> 00:14:07.320
Paris or Mom?

147
00:14:08.280 --> 00:14:09.281
Both.

148
00:14:10.449 --> 00:14:11.992
It's good you came.

149
00:14:12.075 --> 00:14:13.660
Find a perch. Keep watch.

150
00:14:13.744 --> 00:14:14.745
Okay.

151
00:14:41.396 --> 00:14:43.774
My guards told me
you'd taken to riding.

152
00:14:45.233 --> 00:14:46.902
I was so pleased to hear it.

153
00:14:48.153 --> 00:14:49.362
With your sight…

154
00:14:51.448 --> 00:14:53.825
you must be able to ride so quickly.

155
00:14:55.619 --> 00:14:56.828
How exhilarating.

156
00:14:57.954 --> 00:14:58.955
I wonder.

157
00:14:59.790 --> 00:15:01.208
would you take me on a ride?

158
00:15:15.639 --> 00:15:17.224
It would mean so much to me.

159
00:15:22.395 --> 00:15:23.396
You okay?

160
00:15:26.733 --> 00:15:28.193
Great.

161
00:16:02.644 --> 00:16:05.522
I haven't felt freedom like that
in such a long time.

162
00:16:07.065 --> 00:16:10.652
Really? You're the queen.

163
00:16:12.195 --> 00:16:13.947
Don't mistake power for freedom.

164
00:16:17.576 --> 00:16:19.202
My position binds me to my people.

165
00:16:19.286 --> 00:16:22.289
but it also keeps me
forever at a distance.

166
00:16:26.001 --> 00:16:27.169
That sounds lonely.

167
00:16:28.545 --> 00:16:31.214
Everyone does as I command. but…

168
00:16:32.841 --> 00:16:35.051
no one laughs with me…

169
00:16:37.429 --> 00:16:38.847
wishes to know how I feel.

170
00:16:38.930 --> 00:16:40.474
Am I happy? Sad?

171
00:16:41.224 --> 00:16:43.977
I'm… I'm the queen.

172
00:16:46.104 --> 00:16:51.109
It's been a very long time since someone
treated me with simple. honest affection.

173
00:17:02.204 --> 00:17:03.205
Thank you.

174
00:17:10.462 --> 00:17:11.630
Should we go again?

175
00:17:28.021 --> 00:17:31.650
For years there was bloody conflict
between our nations.

176
00:17:31.733 --> 00:17:34.486
But for a long while. the peace has held.

177
00:17:34.569 --> 00:17:37.489
And now we hear
your queen has assembled a war council.

178
00:17:38.824 --> 00:17:39.950
Know this now.

179
00:17:40.909 --> 00:17:44.746
it will be a sorry day for all Payans
if we answer this call to arms.

180
00:17:45.789 --> 00:17:48.750
But we have no particular desire
to go to war.

181
00:17:48.834 --> 00:17:51.169
Perhaps once you explain
your queen's behavior.

182
00:17:51.253 --> 00:17:53.672
we can reach a less bloody solution.

183
00:17:53.755 --> 00:17:57.134
The queen has responded
to Trivantian aggression.

184
00:17:57.717 --> 00:18:00.137
Your soldiers have been encroaching
on our land.

185
00:18:00.220 --> 00:18:03.432
occupying border towns
and taking our people as slaves.

186
00:18:03.932 --> 00:18:05.892
If your accusations were true.

187
00:18:05.975 --> 00:18:08.270
we could talk about settling them.

188
00:18:08.353 --> 00:18:12.983
But Trivantian law prohibits any slaving
company from crossing the eastern border.

189
00:18:13.817 --> 00:18:16.111
And we have occupied no Payan towns

190
00:18:16.611 --> 00:18:20.156
except in retaliation
to military incursions

191
00:18:20.240 --> 00:18:22.032
and smuggling across our borders.

192
00:18:22.117 --> 00:18:23.618
It's hard to talk about borders

193
00:18:23.702 --> 00:18:28.206
when your government has repeatedly
re-knotted the surveyors' maps.

194
00:18:28.290 --> 00:18:30.667
claiming Payan territory as your own.

195
00:18:30.751 --> 00:18:34.087
To be clear. is that a formal accusation?

196
00:18:34.171 --> 00:18:35.547
It's a fact.

197
00:18:36.131 --> 00:18:37.299
I know that voice.

198
00:18:38.633 --> 00:18:40.051
That's Wren.

199
00:18:40.135 --> 00:18:42.012
The woman who saved us in Trivantes.

200
00:18:45.515 --> 00:18:47.267
Sounds like you're happy to see her.

201
00:18:49.728 --> 00:18:50.729
I am.

202
00:18:57.360 --> 00:18:59.070
It's always the hard way with you.

203
00:19:06.119 --> 00:19:07.954
If this was a simple border dispute.

204
00:19:08.038 --> 00:19:11.958
perhaps you'd just review the maps
and agree on our respective territories.

205
00:19:12.042 --> 00:19:13.627
Yes. but…

206
00:19:15.879 --> 00:19:18.673
any peace must come
with an official apology

207
00:19:18.757 --> 00:19:20.258
for the attack on Kanzua.

208
00:19:20.759 --> 00:19:23.345
An apology? You can't be serious.

209
00:19:23.428 --> 00:19:26.056
We will not apologize
for something we did not do.

210
00:19:26.139 --> 00:19:29.142
You destroyed the dam
and tried to murder our queen.

211
00:19:29.226 --> 00:19:30.560
We did no such thing!

212
00:19:30.644 --> 00:19:33.063
Come on. We're talking a simple apology.

213
00:19:33.146 --> 00:19:36.483
We are the strongest military power
on the continent.

214
00:19:36.566 --> 00:19:39.236
If we wanted your queen dead.
she'd be dead.

215
00:19:39.319 --> 00:19:41.738
It's that strength that makes you
the only nation

216
00:19:41.822 --> 00:19:43.990
capable of pulling off
an attack on Kanzua.

217
00:19:44.074 --> 00:19:46.660
Your queen is despised by many of her own.

218
00:19:46.743 --> 00:19:49.871
I would not be surprised
if this so-called attack

219
00:19:49.955 --> 00:19:51.915
came from within her own camp.

220
00:19:51.998 --> 00:19:56.169
Regardless. we will not take the blame
for something we did not do.

221
00:19:56.253 --> 00:20:00.048
just as we will stand by any actions
we did take in defense of our nation.

222
00:20:00.966 --> 00:20:03.385
For instance. Lord Harlan.

223
00:20:03.927 --> 00:20:06.054
we made no secret
of beheading your brother

224
00:20:06.138 --> 00:20:08.807
after he was caught spying in our city.

225
00:20:09.808 --> 00:20:11.476
As a matter of fact.

226
00:20:11.560 --> 00:20:13.937
we sent his head back to you
as a courtesy.

227
00:20:14.938 --> 00:20:17.941
We tried to make it quick.
but he refused to cooperate.

228
00:20:21.153 --> 00:20:23.321
- Captain Gosset!
- I'll kill you!

229
00:20:23.822 --> 00:20:24.906
Come on!

230
00:20:27.075 --> 00:20:28.702
All right. That's enough.

231
00:20:28.785 --> 00:20:29.953
Have you lost your mind?

232
00:20:30.036 --> 00:20:31.955
-Fuck you!
-I want him arrested at once!

233
00:20:32.038 --> 00:20:35.125
This is a peace summit on neutral grounds.
There will be no arrests!

234
00:20:35.208 --> 00:20:37.085
- Shove a poker up your ass!
- I apologize.

235
00:20:37.169 --> 00:20:38.587
Don't apologize to them.

236
00:20:38.670 --> 00:20:40.964
This conference was a waste of time.
We're done here.

237
00:20:41.047 --> 00:20:43.091
Are you leaving? Oh. no.

238
00:20:43.967 --> 00:20:45.427
Bye-bye. Good night.

239
00:20:45.510 --> 00:20:48.430
Sweet dreams. assholes.

240
00:20:51.516 --> 00:20:52.517
Whoo.

241
00:21:15.248 --> 00:21:19.169
-Paris.
-Most people chop firewood outside.

242
00:21:21.254 --> 00:21:22.714
I'm doing sword drills.

243
00:21:24.049 --> 00:21:28.470
And… you just do the same motion over
and over until it becomes thoughtless.

244
00:21:29.346 --> 00:21:32.099
In battle. there's no time to think.

245
00:21:32.182 --> 00:21:36.019
Mmm. Did Toad teach you that?

246
00:21:36.103 --> 00:21:38.021
No. it's a fundamental rule of combat.

247
00:21:38.563 --> 00:21:39.564
Huh.

248
00:21:44.152 --> 00:21:45.153
Remember…

249
00:21:46.822 --> 00:21:50.575
there are weapons more powerful
than swords. Hmm?

250
00:21:51.410 --> 00:21:54.371
Compassion. love--

251
00:21:54.454 --> 00:21:56.248
Love didn't save our people.

252
00:22:01.128 --> 00:22:03.088
I sense you're different. Kofun.

253
00:22:05.424 --> 00:22:07.134
So much anger.

254
00:22:07.801 --> 00:22:09.719
Of course I'm angry.

255
00:22:10.595 --> 00:22:12.514
I've been lied to my entire life.

256
00:22:19.646 --> 00:22:21.898
You've spent time with the queen.

257
00:22:23.942 --> 00:22:27.863
Be careful. Be very careful. my dear.

258
00:22:28.822 --> 00:22:29.990
This queen…

259
00:22:32.826 --> 00:22:34.619
serves only one interest.

260
00:22:36.872 --> 00:22:37.873
Her own.

261
00:22:38.540 --> 00:22:41.084
Or maybe she's just careful
about who she trusts.

262
00:22:44.629 --> 00:22:45.630
Mmm.

263
00:22:47.132 --> 00:22:49.801
Well. at least she doesn't pretend to be
someone she's not.

264
00:22:52.345 --> 00:22:53.346
I'm busy. Paris.

265
00:23:04.566 --> 00:23:06.651
You both need to calm down.

266
00:23:07.152 --> 00:23:08.653
No harm was done.

267
00:23:09.279 --> 00:23:10.280
No harm?

268
00:23:11.198 --> 00:23:13.158
You almost started the war right there.

269
00:23:13.241 --> 00:23:15.702
I may have had a bad moment. granted--

270
00:23:15.786 --> 00:23:18.580
Your bad moment has ended
any chance of a negotiated peace.

271
00:23:18.663 --> 00:23:21.708
Well. if that's true. why haven't
the Trivantians ridden off yet?

272
00:23:23.001 --> 00:23:24.002
Ha!

273
00:23:25.003 --> 00:23:28.131
Maghra. you're new to this.

274
00:23:29.216 --> 00:23:30.550
And. Boo-Boo.

275
00:23:30.634 --> 00:23:34.012
you don't strike me as the kind of guy
to negotiate his way out of a fight.

276
00:23:34.096 --> 00:23:36.556
So you'll both have to trust me
when I tell you

277
00:23:36.640 --> 00:23:38.475
we've gained invaluable knowledge.

278
00:23:38.558 --> 00:23:39.559
And what is that?

279
00:23:39.643 --> 00:23:42.771
The Trivantians might actually be serious
about peace.

280
00:23:42.854 --> 00:23:44.648
They will never return to the table.

281
00:23:44.731 --> 00:23:46.858
Yeah. well. they will.

282
00:23:46.942 --> 00:23:48.777
But the table doesn't matter.

283
00:23:49.736 --> 00:23:53.657
What matters is the deal you make
before you get to the table.

284
00:23:55.075 --> 00:23:56.410
What are you talking about?

285
00:23:58.620 --> 00:24:00.914
What have you done without my authority?

286
00:24:00.997 --> 00:24:02.874
I acted in your name

287
00:24:02.958 --> 00:24:06.169
and with your best interests at heart.
Princess.

288
00:24:06.253 --> 00:24:08.755
We have a meeting tonight
with Ambassador Scopus.

289
00:24:08.839 --> 00:24:09.923
It's a private meeting.

290
00:24:10.006 --> 00:24:14.845
away from the bluster
and the threats and Torrance's spying.

291
00:24:16.721 --> 00:24:18.390
We negotiate the peace tonight.

292
00:24:19.599 --> 00:24:23.562
and then we pretend to do it again
at the table in the morning.

293
00:24:25.981 --> 00:24:27.691
You will not go to this meeting.

294
00:24:27.774 --> 00:24:29.025
Excuse me?

295
00:24:29.609 --> 00:24:32.112
You mean my meeting that I set up for me?

296
00:24:32.195 --> 00:24:33.447
Yeah. I think I will.

297
00:24:33.530 --> 00:24:36.283
No. You have another one
of your bad moments.

298
00:24:36.366 --> 00:24:38.577
you and Maghra will be dead right there.

299
00:24:38.660 --> 00:24:39.661
I will go with her.

300
00:24:39.745 --> 00:24:40.912
Oh. yeah.

301
00:24:40.996 --> 00:24:44.791
A Trivantian traitor wanted for murder.
What could possibly go wrong?

302
00:24:44.875 --> 00:24:47.461
Just-- Just stop it. both of you.

303
00:24:52.674 --> 00:24:55.218
Lord Harlan. that is the last time

304
00:24:55.302 --> 00:24:58.680
you will negotiate anything on my behalf
without my express permission.

305
00:24:58.764 --> 00:24:59.890
Is that understood?

306
00:25:01.850 --> 00:25:03.643
-Is that understood?
-Yes.

307
00:25:05.687 --> 00:25:07.773
Now.

308
00:25:09.024 --> 00:25:10.484
This is how we move forward.

309
00:25:11.985 --> 00:25:14.988
Harlan. you will attend the meeting
with me. but so will Baba Voss.

310
00:25:15.072 --> 00:25:16.865
And if you speak one word out of line.

311
00:25:16.948 --> 00:25:19.993
he will render you speechless
with a method of his choice.

312
00:25:25.332 --> 00:25:27.584
Now. where is this meeting
you've arranged?

313
00:26:30.480 --> 00:26:34.651
You forgot to mention
you were Payan royalty.

314
00:26:37.988 --> 00:26:41.116
I would have… if I had known.

315
00:26:42.367 --> 00:26:43.368
You didn't know?

316
00:26:44.911 --> 00:26:46.329
It's a long story.

317
00:26:46.413 --> 00:26:47.414
Hmm.

318
00:26:48.290 --> 00:26:50.417
Well. you'll have to tell me sometime.

319
00:26:56.465 --> 00:27:01.052
Every day since I escaped.
I've dreamed of seeing you again.

320
00:27:03.054 --> 00:27:04.347
I know this is difficult.

321
00:27:07.142 --> 00:27:08.810
Our nations are about to go to war.

322
00:27:08.894 --> 00:27:10.896
Not if this conference is successful.

323
00:27:13.857 --> 00:27:14.858
It won't be.

324
00:27:15.358 --> 00:27:16.568
You can't know that.

325
00:27:18.779 --> 00:27:19.780
Can you?

326
00:27:20.781 --> 00:27:24.618
And if our people go to war…

327
00:27:26.953 --> 00:27:29.998
…you will fight for yours.
and I will fight for mine.

328
00:27:30.082 --> 00:27:32.209
We just can't let that happen. Wren.

329
00:27:34.795 --> 00:27:36.546
I know my mother doesn't want war.

330
00:27:38.048 --> 00:27:41.468
I'm not sure there can be peace…

331
00:27:43.303 --> 00:27:44.554
between our people.

332
00:27:50.143 --> 00:27:53.688
And I don't wanna fight you.

333
00:27:55.232 --> 00:27:56.233
Wren.

334
00:28:09.079 --> 00:28:10.664
I will never fight you.

335
00:28:34.729 --> 00:28:35.730
Scopus?

336
00:28:37.149 --> 00:28:38.150
You here?

337
00:28:40.318 --> 00:28:41.903
Where else would I be?

338
00:28:45.782 --> 00:28:48.702
Harlan. And who is with you?

339
00:28:48.785 --> 00:28:50.620
As promised. brought the princess.

340
00:28:50.704 --> 00:28:52.831
- Princess.
- Ambassador.

341
00:28:52.914 --> 00:28:55.667
Please let me offer
my most sincere apologies

342
00:28:55.751 --> 00:28:58.128
for Lord Harlan's inexcusable outburst.

343
00:28:58.211 --> 00:29:01.965
You did make a fool of yourself. Harlan.
acting out like a temperamental child.

344
00:29:02.048 --> 00:29:03.967
Imagine if you'd actually harmed Watts.

345
00:29:04.050 --> 00:29:06.428
Come on.
It's not a summit till someone gets hit.

346
00:29:08.013 --> 00:29:10.682
So… we gonna do this?

347
00:29:10.766 --> 00:29:11.892
Where do we begin?

348
00:29:12.726 --> 00:29:14.436
We know you didn't attack Kanzua.

349
00:29:14.519 --> 00:29:16.229
Princess. I appreciate your candor.

350
00:29:16.313 --> 00:29:18.482
A refreshing change from earlier today.

351
00:29:18.565 --> 00:29:21.485
but I didn't need to crawl down here
to hear what I already know.

352
00:29:21.568 --> 00:29:23.528
Then I'll tell you something
you don't know.

353
00:29:24.196 --> 00:29:27.866
Within a very short time.
my sister will no longer be queen.

354
00:29:30.202 --> 00:29:31.286
I'm listening.

355
00:29:31.787 --> 00:29:34.706
The queen has not been herself
since the fall of Kanzua.

356
00:29:34.790 --> 00:29:38.960
She has suffered greatly.
and her judgment has become questionable.

357
00:29:39.044 --> 00:29:40.504
And your judgment is more sound?

358
00:29:40.587 --> 00:29:42.672
There'll be no victor
in a war between our countries.

359
00:29:42.756 --> 00:29:44.758
I'm quite confident there would be.

360
00:29:44.841 --> 00:29:47.886
You're asking my government to apologize
for an attack we did not commit.

361
00:29:47.969 --> 00:29:50.263
When I am queen.
I will disavow the apology

362
00:29:50.347 --> 00:29:51.681
and make the truth known.

363
00:29:51.765 --> 00:29:53.558
Why would I agree to this?

364
00:29:53.642 --> 00:29:55.811
For the same reason
you're here at all.

365
00:29:55.894 --> 00:29:59.481
We all know the Triangle does not want
a second war.

366
00:29:59.564 --> 00:30:00.857
You turn your back on the Ganites.

367
00:30:00.941 --> 00:30:02.984
and they'll be through your walls
in a matter of weeks.

368
00:30:03.068 --> 00:30:04.653
The Ganites are cockroaches

369
00:30:04.736 --> 00:30:07.197
and crushed under our boots
on a daily basis.

370
00:30:07.280 --> 00:30:09.825
And all those boots are mobilized
in the west.

371
00:30:11.076 --> 00:30:13.995
It would be a grave error
to underestimate our capabilities.

372
00:30:14.079 --> 00:30:15.330
Yeah. I know.

373
00:30:17.165 --> 00:30:19.876
But you know
our queen is capable of such errors.

374
00:30:21.920 --> 00:30:23.213
So. do we have a deal?

375
00:30:25.549 --> 00:30:28.677
So. Harlan.
you've married yourself a future queen.

376
00:30:28.760 --> 00:30:31.346
- Hmm.
- A bold gamble. even for you.

377
00:30:32.055 --> 00:30:36.518
Well. we're all slaves to the vagaries
of true love.

378
00:30:45.861 --> 00:30:47.446
Thank you for dining with me.

379
00:30:48.113 --> 00:30:50.323
Gets so quiet when everyone's away.

380
00:30:58.790 --> 00:31:02.627
Thank you for the ride this morning.

381
00:31:04.087 --> 00:31:05.130
It was nothing.

382
00:31:05.630 --> 00:31:06.798
It was not nothing.

383
00:31:08.925 --> 00:31:10.260
I'd like to return the favor.

384
00:31:10.343 --> 00:31:12.220
-Harmony?
-Your Highness?

385
00:31:12.721 --> 00:31:13.889
Do you have it?

386
00:31:14.389 --> 00:31:16.641
Yes. a portion for each of you.

387
00:31:27.402 --> 00:31:29.738
Your service is a blessing.

388
00:31:29.821 --> 00:31:30.906
Thank you. my Queen.

389
00:31:34.910 --> 00:31:36.828
Have you had thornflower before?

390
00:31:37.662 --> 00:31:39.039
The journeyer?

391
00:31:39.623 --> 00:31:40.832
It's forbidden.

392
00:31:40.916 --> 00:31:43.919
I won't tell if you don't.

393
00:31:46.338 --> 00:31:48.048
I've never taken journeyers before.

394
00:31:49.549 --> 00:31:51.927
I'm honored to take your first journey
with you.

395
00:31:55.388 --> 00:31:56.765
What are its effects?

396
00:31:57.724 --> 00:32:02.813
I cannot explain it to you
any more than you can explain sight to me.

397
00:32:05.482 --> 00:32:07.234
I'll give you the same amount I take.

398
00:32:07.317 --> 00:32:09.611
Surely a man your size can handle that.

399
00:32:18.453 --> 00:32:19.621
Now me.

400
00:32:38.974 --> 00:32:41.309
Mmm.

401
00:32:42.477 --> 00:32:43.770
Mmm.

402
00:32:44.980 --> 00:32:46.356
And now we wait.

403
00:33:18.513 --> 00:33:20.974
I don't feel anything.

404
00:33:25.187 --> 00:33:29.357
To feel. you have to touch.

405
00:33:29.441 --> 00:33:30.609
Touch?

406
00:33:40.702 --> 00:33:42.037
-Mmm.
-Oh.

407
00:33:43.830 --> 00:33:45.707
Yeah. I feel. uh…

408
00:33:45.791 --> 00:33:47.375
I-- I feel…

409
00:33:47.459 --> 00:33:49.211
Not like that. Kofun.

410
00:34:16.279 --> 00:34:18.156
Do you feel that?

411
00:34:19.282 --> 00:34:20.450
Yes.

412
00:34:29.459 --> 00:34:32.295
Mmm.

413
00:34:37.467 --> 00:34:40.929
Oh. I feel that.

414
00:34:56.445 --> 00:34:58.405
-Sibeth.
-Mmm?

415
00:34:59.781 --> 00:35:01.032
Sibeth.

416
00:35:05.036 --> 00:35:06.705
Should I stop?

417
00:35:11.668 --> 00:35:12.668
No.

418
00:35:48.996 --> 00:35:51.625
Oh!

419
00:36:37.337 --> 00:36:38.755
<i>So. what do you think?</i>

420
00:36:39.798 --> 00:36:41.800
Scopus will make the deal.
Trust me.

421
00:36:41.883 --> 00:36:44.302
- I don't trust you or him.
- Hey. Baba.

422
00:36:44.386 --> 00:36:48.348
Ask your husband how it is he has the ear
of a high-ranking Trivantian ambassador.

423
00:36:48.432 --> 00:36:50.976
He does make a good point. Harlan.
It is suspicious.

424
00:36:51.059 --> 00:36:52.352
I'm no spy.

425
00:36:53.061 --> 00:36:54.187
So. what then?

426
00:36:56.481 --> 00:36:59.484
The queen's tax.
It's fucking high and stupid.

427
00:37:00.318 --> 00:37:04.489
So. in order to keep the city fortified
and keep my citizens fed in leaner times.

428
00:37:04.573 --> 00:37:08.285
I occasionally have to make the odd deal
beyond the reach of Kanzua.

429
00:37:09.119 --> 00:37:10.746
It's thornflower. Coal.

430
00:37:11.329 --> 00:37:12.581
So. you broke the law?

431
00:37:13.123 --> 00:37:16.543
Cute. Yeah. I broke the law for my people.

432
00:37:18.086 --> 00:37:20.881
Mmm. No doubt taking a good percentage
for your efforts.

433
00:37:20.964 --> 00:37:23.675
A fair one. The risk was all mine.

434
00:37:25.177 --> 00:37:28.346
Look. we all have our questionable pasts.
don't we?

435
00:37:28.847 --> 00:37:30.599
And you should be grateful for mine.

436
00:37:30.682 --> 00:37:33.518
because otherwise
we'd all be skipping off to war right now.

437
00:37:34.019 --> 00:37:39.357
So. Baba Voss. unless you got
any more pretty little threats for me.

438
00:37:39.441 --> 00:37:40.734
I'm gonna go to sleep.

439
00:37:41.568 --> 00:37:44.571
We have a peace to pretend to negotiate
in the morning.

440
00:37:46.031 --> 00:37:48.366
It's been a long day.
We should all go to bed.

441
00:37:50.118 --> 00:37:51.787
We can argue more tomorrow.

442
00:37:53.121 --> 00:37:54.206
Uh. excuse me.

443
00:37:56.083 --> 00:37:57.375
Get out of my way.

444
00:37:58.001 --> 00:37:59.002
No.

445
00:38:00.337 --> 00:38:02.130
How we sleep in private is one thing.

446
00:38:02.214 --> 00:38:04.591
but Scopus just made a deal

447
00:38:04.674 --> 00:38:07.719
with queen-to-be Maghra
and her king-to-be Harlan.

448
00:38:08.386 --> 00:38:10.555
Can't let anything confuse that. can we?

449
00:38:20.524 --> 00:38:21.733
If you touch her…

450
00:38:24.569 --> 00:38:28.198
One of these days.
I'm gonna make you finish that sentence.

451
00:38:29.282 --> 00:38:30.700
I'll sleep out here with you.

452
00:38:32.035 --> 00:38:34.621
- Oh.
- What?

453
00:38:35.747 --> 00:38:37.499
Oh.

454
00:38:41.461 --> 00:38:43.255
He's a jackass. but he's right.

455
00:38:45.799 --> 00:38:48.051
I don't want to be the reason
for your failure.

456
00:38:51.388 --> 00:38:53.306
It's too cold for you out here anyways.

457
00:38:54.599 --> 00:38:55.600
Go in.

458
00:38:57.936 --> 00:38:59.020
You sure?

459
00:39:00.564 --> 00:39:03.233
Yes.

460
00:40:05.796 --> 00:40:08.423
We all know
Trivantes did not attack Kanzua.

461
00:40:09.382 --> 00:40:13.804
But we also know your queen is
deranged enough to go to war anyway.

462
00:40:14.721 --> 00:40:19.101
So. we will deal with her the way
you deal with a child having a tantrum.

463
00:40:19.935 --> 00:40:21.728
In the interests of peace.

464
00:40:22.354 --> 00:40:24.439
we will grant her the apology she craves.

465
00:40:25.440 --> 00:40:27.150
Thank you. Ambassador.

466
00:40:27.234 --> 00:40:29.611
And in exchange for this lie.

467
00:40:29.694 --> 00:40:33.198
you will accept the borders
as they are knotted on our maps.

468
00:40:33.698 --> 00:40:34.699
Agreed?

469
00:40:35.367 --> 00:40:38.620
We accept your proposal and thank you
on behalf of the Payan people.

470
00:40:39.121 --> 00:40:40.122
Excellent.

471
00:40:40.705 --> 00:40:42.874
Our clerks will have the day
to redraw the maps.

472
00:40:42.958 --> 00:40:45.085
and we'll review them tomorrow
before we depart.

473
00:40:46.837 --> 00:40:48.755
Uh. one more thing before we adjourn.

474
00:40:49.256 --> 00:40:52.426
This. uh.
business of your queen embracing sight.

475
00:40:53.802 --> 00:40:55.554
that must end.

476
00:40:56.847 --> 00:41:00.100
If the sighted are allowed to grow
and prosper there.

477
00:41:00.183 --> 00:41:03.854
no amount of border concessions
will save you from destruction.

478
00:41:30.672 --> 00:41:31.882
Hello. Paris.

479
00:41:35.469 --> 00:41:36.470
Hello.

480
00:41:46.104 --> 00:41:48.440
I don't recall inviting you to join me.

481
00:41:49.149 --> 00:41:50.942
I didn't want you to dine alone.

482
00:41:52.068 --> 00:41:54.237
Maybe I like dining alone.

483
00:41:54.321 --> 00:41:56.239
No one likes dining alone.

484
00:41:59.743 --> 00:42:05.415
When I asked you to stay close to Kofun.
I did not mean turn him into a soldier.

485
00:42:06.958 --> 00:42:08.960
Believe me. there's no risk of that.

486
00:42:09.044 --> 00:42:12.339
I'm serious. He is under your care.

487
00:42:12.839 --> 00:42:16.218
It is your responsibility to--
to guide him.

488
00:42:16.301 --> 00:42:18.386
I'm teaching a boy how to protect himself.

489
00:42:18.470 --> 00:42:19.888
-nothing more.
-Toad.

490
00:42:19.971 --> 00:42:22.349
My whole life.
I was taught to kill witches.

491
00:42:22.432 --> 00:42:24.476
Now you tell me I must protect them.

492
00:42:25.852 --> 00:42:26.853
Hmm?

493
00:42:27.437 --> 00:42:28.814
So. why should I trust you?

494
00:42:28.897 --> 00:42:30.816
You must trust yourself.

495
00:42:33.110 --> 00:42:36.947
You. and you alone. are responsible
for every choice you make. man.

496
00:42:37.030 --> 00:42:38.281
What if I choose wrong?

497
00:42:39.449 --> 00:42:40.659
You won't.

498
00:42:40.742 --> 00:42:41.827
How do you know?

499
00:42:46.540 --> 00:42:47.541
Because…

500
00:42:49.584 --> 00:42:53.588
I can tell you are a good man…

501
00:42:57.259 --> 00:42:58.760
with a very stupid name.

502
00:43:05.600 --> 00:43:06.601
Good man.

503
00:43:22.743 --> 00:43:23.744
Good morning.

504
00:43:25.495 --> 00:43:26.496
Hi.

505
00:43:48.477 --> 00:43:50.103
Are you regretting last night?

506
00:43:53.774 --> 00:43:57.152
I-- I've just never done that before.

507
00:44:03.575 --> 00:44:05.368
What is new is always frightening…

508
00:44:06.912 --> 00:44:08.080
but also exciting.

509
00:44:13.335 --> 00:44:16.755
I wouldn't wanna do anything
that makes you uncomfortable.

510
00:44:20.634 --> 00:44:22.803
These days that seems to be everything.

511
00:44:27.474 --> 00:44:28.725
You've had a hard time.

512
00:44:31.978 --> 00:44:33.396
You don't know who to trust.

513
00:44:38.693 --> 00:44:40.529
Let's make a pact. right now.

514
00:44:40.612 --> 00:44:42.322
I will never lie to you.

515
00:44:45.117 --> 00:44:46.451
You will never lie to me.

516
00:44:47.661 --> 00:44:51.665
Even when the things we tell each other
might be painful to hear.

517
00:44:54.292 --> 00:44:55.293
Agreed?

518
00:44:57.796 --> 00:44:58.797
Agreed.

519
00:45:06.638 --> 00:45:07.931
This peace…

520
00:45:09.683 --> 00:45:12.018
it's built on so many lies.

521
00:45:15.647 --> 00:45:16.982
And it won't stand.

522
00:45:18.525 --> 00:45:21.111
Maybe there's a greater truth
beyond all the lies.

523
00:45:25.657 --> 00:45:26.908
And what truth is that?

524
00:45:29.202 --> 00:45:30.662
That no one wants war.

525
00:45:35.876 --> 00:45:37.919
I wish I was as hopeful as you are.

526
00:45:39.546 --> 00:45:40.547
Well…

527
00:45:42.716 --> 00:45:45.427
if you stay close. maybe it will rub off.

528
00:49:45.208 --> 00:49:47.961
Intruders! Wake up!

529
00:49:49.504 --> 00:49:50.547
What's happening?

530
00:50:24.247 --> 00:50:25.332
Commander Watts?

531
00:50:27.250 --> 00:50:28.376
Who's there?

532
00:50:35.967 --> 00:50:38.470
Who's--

533
00:50:50.524 --> 00:50:54.277
Help! Help! Guards!

534
00:50:54.361 --> 00:50:55.654
We've been betrayed!

535
00:51:13.088 --> 00:51:14.089
Scopus.

536
00:51:16.591 --> 00:51:17.592
I'm sorry.

537
00:51:17.676 --> 00:51:20.095
- No.
- Wren.

538
00:51:24.182 --> 00:51:26.476
Papa. stay back!

539
00:51:28.812 --> 00:51:31.398
You. You did this.

540
00:51:31.481 --> 00:51:34.025
Wren. No.

541
00:51:34.109 --> 00:51:35.652
This was your plan all along.

542
00:51:35.735 --> 00:51:37.404
No. it wasn't us.

543
00:51:37.487 --> 00:51:40.115
You knew I was the only one
who could stop this.

544
00:51:40.198 --> 00:51:42.409
-Wren.
-You kept me up there.

545
00:51:44.536 --> 00:51:46.037
You used me.

546
00:51:46.121 --> 00:51:48.582
No. No.

547
00:51:52.502 --> 00:51:53.503
Wren. wait!

548
00:52:19.404 --> 00:52:21.406
This assassin has Payan markings.

549
00:52:25.160 --> 00:52:26.161
Sibeth.

550
00:52:31.583 --> 00:52:32.584
Shit.

551
00:52:34.419 --> 00:52:36.129
She was never gonna allow a treaty.

552
00:52:36.213 --> 00:52:39.966
This whole summit was just a way
for her to wage a war we couldn't stop.

553
00:52:44.012 --> 00:52:45.555
I almost admire her.

554
00:52:46.807 --> 00:52:49.392
if it weren't for the fact
she's gonna get us all killed.

555
00:52:49.476 --> 00:52:50.560
We need to move.

556
00:52:51.269 --> 00:52:54.022
The Trivantians will be here
before the God Flame rises.

557
00:53:18.046 --> 00:53:19.047
Kofun?

558
00:53:22.217 --> 00:53:23.218
Kofun?

559
00:53:26.930 --> 00:53:27.931
Sibeth.

560
00:53:31.977 --> 00:53:33.437
I'm so sorry to wake you.

561
00:53:34.062 --> 00:53:35.439
No. what's wrong?

562
00:53:35.522 --> 00:53:37.691
Something's happening. I'm not safe here.

563
00:53:38.817 --> 00:53:41.361
What-- What's-- What is it?
What's happening?

564
00:53:41.445 --> 00:53:44.906
Well. nothing yet. but something will.
I'm sure of it.

565
00:53:47.617 --> 00:53:49.369
You are the only one I trust.

566
00:53:56.918 --> 00:53:58.420
Y-You can stay with me.

567
00:54:00.756 --> 00:54:01.757
Thank you.

568
00:55:28.677 --> 00:55:30.011
How was your trip?

569
00:55:49.364 --> 00:55:50.824
You don't seem surprised.

570
00:55:51.908 --> 00:55:55.829
That Queen Kane wanted war?
No. I'm not surprised.

571
00:55:56.997 --> 00:55:58.498
I tried to warn the Triangle.

572
00:56:01.251 --> 00:56:03.003
Those soldiers didn't have to die.

573
00:56:03.879 --> 00:56:06.381
There's something else
you should know.

574
00:56:09.384 --> 00:56:10.677
The attack…

575
00:56:11.678 --> 00:56:13.680
I believe it was led by Baba Voss.

576
00:56:15.223 --> 00:56:17.684
So Baba and his children fight
for the queen now.

577
00:56:19.644 --> 00:56:23.106
It was I who drew him here
and let him escape.

578
00:56:24.816 --> 00:56:27.611
If this gets out.
the Triangle will call for my head.

579
00:56:27.694 --> 00:56:29.279
They will not hear it from me.

580
00:56:32.908 --> 00:56:37.037
You're the only survivor.
The Triangle will have questions.

581
00:56:39.706 --> 00:56:41.833
The first of those questions will be:

582
00:56:43.877 --> 00:56:48.090
How is it that the lone survivor
of the attack was my own captain?

583
00:56:50.717 --> 00:56:51.968
You think I'm a traitor?

584
00:56:53.220 --> 00:56:55.472
No. Of course not.

585
00:56:56.807 --> 00:56:58.725
I've known you since you were a child.

586
00:57:01.353 --> 00:57:04.356
Still. the ground does continue to shift
under our feet.

587
00:57:04.856 --> 00:57:08.110
So I need to know
the answer to this question. Captain.

588
00:57:11.905 --> 00:57:14.825
How is it that you alone survived?

589
00:57:16.368 --> 00:57:18.766
-I would have thought you would be glad--
-Answer me.

590
00:58:06.743 --> 00:58:08.196
Because I can see.

590
00:58:09.305 --> 00:59:09.152
